abstract: Congressional elections of 2012 will have the largest number of female incumbents ever up for re-election in the Senate and would be among the highest number of female nominees ever; given the political vulnerabilities of many of the candidate, it could also turn out to be the first time in a generation that women lose ground in the Senate.
snippet: More female incumbents than ever are up for re-election in the Senate, but if Democrats have a bad year, women could, too.
lead_paragraph: More female incumbents than ever are up for re-election in the Senate, but if Democrats have a bad year, women could, too.

headline.main: More Women in Senate, but Seats Are at Risk
headline.print_headline: More Women In Senate, But Seats Are at Risk
headline.seo: More Women Than Ever in Senate, but Their Seats Are at Risk
